This code is implemented to add texts to the desired video files (.mp4 or .avi)
For other video formats the necessary FOURCC code can be added into the modifyV$

In order to execute the code, install python3.7 and opencv2 if necessary

execution with minimum parameters: python3 text_adding.py video_name
For additional parameters, have a look at the following

usage: text_adding.py [-h] [-d DURATION] [-t TEXT] [--text_color TEXT_COLOR]
                      [--bg_color BG_COLOR] [--alpha ALPHA] [--scale SCALE]
                      [-o OUTPUT] [-p POSITION POSITION]
                      video

Video Text Adding

positional arguments:
  video                 path of the video

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -d DURATION, --duration DURATION
                        text duration in seconds
  -t TEXT, --text TEXT  text to be added. default random
  --text_color TEXT_COLOR
                        color of the text eg. '(50,50,50)'
  --bg_color BG_COLOR   color of the text background eg. '(50,50,50)'
  --alpha ALPHA         transparency of the text background (default 90
                        percent)
  --scale SCALE         scale of the text font
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        name of the output file
  -p POSITION POSITION, --position POSITION POSITION
                        x,y coordinates of the text location in the form 'x
                        y'. default random
